Weak to moderate cytoplasmic positivity was seen in most malignant tissues. Malignant lymphomas were negative.

Cancer tissues were generally negative. Cases of pancreatic, gastric and liver cancers exhibited moderate cytoplasmic positivity.

tissueExpression.summary: Most of the normal tissues displayed moderate cytoplasmic positivity. Subset of cells in intestinal tract, renal tubules, lung macrophages, myoepithelial cells, plasma and fraction of cells in seminiferous ducts showed strong staining. Decidual cells, prostate, spleen and tonsil were negative.

Most of the cancer tissues displayed moderate cytoplasmic positivity. Isolated cases of hepatocellular carcinomas, breast, cervical, endometrial, pancreatic and stomach cancers showed strong staining. Several gliomas, lymphomas, melanomas, lung and skin cancers were negative.

tissueExpression.summary: Gastrointestinal tract, bronchus, hepatocytes, kidney, exocrine pancreas, adrenal gland, squamous epithelia, postmenopausal uterine glands, cervix, heart muscle and seminal vesicle showed moderate to strong cytoplasmic positivity in fraction of cells. Remaining normal tissues were weakly stained or negative.

Cancer tissues displayed moderate to strong cytoplasmic positivity in fraction of tumor cells. Lymphomas along with majority cases of gliomas, melanomas, endometrial, breast, renal, testicular, urothelial, squamous and basal cell carcinomas were weakly stained or negative.
